and don't leave your name?

248
00:26:01,800 --> 00:26:06,600
- Even a dumb geezer knows ...
- Just move on. No one was killed.

249
00:26:06,700 --> 00:26:08,900
Ask him.

250
00:26:09,700 --> 00:26:13,400
Don't bark at me.
I didn't name you.

251
00:26:13,600 --> 00:26:17,600
We will. And if he can't,
we'll come back and ask you.

252
00:26:17,700 --> 00:26:24,700
Hey. I come from hell. My grandma
has got more attitude than you.

253
00:26:24,900 --> 00:26:28,500
Go shake down a 7-1 1
for a day-old wiener.

254
00:26:28,700 --> 00:26:33,200
There's a painting
of one of the guys.

255
00:26:35,900 --> 00:26:41,500
- I've been praying for him.
- I'm on my way to the hospital.

256
00:26:41,700 --> 00:26:45,900
- Just watch the dog for tonight.
- No, no.

257
00:26:46,100 --> 00:26:48,900
- I'm sorry.
- Thanks.

258
00:26:50,500 --> 00:26:54,800
Old bitch. Damn dog.

259
00:26:58,100 --> 00:27:00,800
You're taking him!

260
00:27:01,000 --> 00:27:03,200
Get out of the way!

261
00:27:03,300 --> 00:27:06,400
Even the books.

262
00:27:07,200 --> 00:27:09,200
Wait!

263
00:27:09,800 --> 00:27:13,500
Do you want to say no to me?

264
00:27:18,800 --> 00:27:22,300
I don't want to say nothing to you.

265
00:27:22,800 --> 00:27:29,300
Because I've never felt this crazy.
I almost want you to say no.

266
00:27:32,700 --> 00:27:34,700
Thanks for looking after him.

267
00:27:34,900 --> 00:27:41,900
- Hey! Where are you going?
- You don't want to mess with me.

268
00:27:42,100 --> 00:27:47,100
I can't take a dog.
Nobody's been in here before.

269
00:27:50,800 --> 00:27:53,300
Hey, Frank.

270
00:28:16,800 --> 00:28:20,100
One, two, three, four ...

271
00:28:39,900 --> 00:28:42,600
You're dead.

272
00:28:42,700 --> 00:28:46,600
We don't have no dog food here.

273
00:28:46,700 --> 00:28:51,300
You'll eat what we got.
What we eat.

274
00:29:00,400 --> 00:29:02,900
Don't you do anything!

275
00:29:17,700 --> 00:29:20,200
Where's the trust?

276
00:29:29,600 --> 00:29:33,000
Never a break.

277
00:30:04,800 --> 00:30:06,800
God!

278
00:30:06,900 --> 00:30:11,700
We're halfway through the show
and we haven't sold a painting.

279
00:30:11,900 --> 00:30:15,200
No, we can't reduce the price.

280
00:30:15,400 --> 00:30:20,500
- I'm in a free fall here.
- We can see him.

281
00:30:21,700 --> 00:30:25,100
I'll meet you in there, okay?

282
00:30:27,200 --> 00:30:29,200
Thank you.

283
00:30:31,900 --> 00:30:36,400
- How are you doing, great one?
- I haven't looked at myself yet.

284
00:30:36,600 --> 00:30:41,200
I figured
I could tell from your reaction.

285
00:30:42,000 --> 00:30:46,000
- That bad?
- I talked to the doctor and ...

286
00:30:49,800 --> 00:30:55,900
It's not that bad. The doctors say
you'll be your old self again.

287
00:30:56,100 --> 00:31:00,600
The scars might ... Oh, shit!

288
00:31:06,400 --> 00:31:08,400
Jackie ...

289
00:31:08,500 --> 00:31:11,700
Hand me a mirror, please.

290
00:31:19,300 --> 00:31:23,200
Wait. I have a smaller one.

291
00:31:33,200 --> 00:31:36,500
So how are things, anyway?

292
00:31:36,700 --> 00:31:42,300
- How is Verdell?
- Mr. Udall ... taking care of him.

293
00:31:42,500 --> 00:31:48,200
- How could you? He'll hurt him.
- No, I promise.

294
00:31:48,300 --> 00:31:53,200
Not a chance. I own this guy.
Besides, there was nobody else.

295
00:31:53,300 --> 00:31:56,300
I'm always on the move and ...

296
00:31:56,500 --> 00:31:59,300
Trust me.

297
00:31:59,500 --> 00:32:04,200
- You are certain my dog is okay?
- Yes, your dog is fine.

298
00:32:11,100 --> 00:32:14,500
Waiting gives the devil time.

299
00:32:31,000 --> 00:32:33,900
Oh, my!

300
00:32:43,700 --> 00:32:46,600
Where did I go?

301
00:32:47,700 --> 00:32:50,900
- That's your dog?
- No.

302
00:32:51,800 --> 00:32:55,000
What are you doing with a dog?

303
00:32:55,300 --> 00:33:00,100
- Suckered in, set up.
- You're not worried he'll be taken?

304
00:33:02,800 --> 00:33:06,300
No, not until now.

305
00:33:06,400 --> 00:33:10,400
- Sorry.
- I'm going to sit here.

306
00:33:10,500 --> 00:33:13,000
Hey, puppy.

307
00:33:13,800 --> 00:33:17,200
It's so cute.

308
00:33:17,400 --> 00:33:20,400
I wonder what breed he is.

309
00:33:24,000 --> 00:33:28,800
He's a little dog. If Bryan's not
here, you can bring him in.

310
00:33:31,500 --> 00:33:34,100
How old are you?

311
00:33:34,300 --> 00:33:37,800
To guess by your eyes ... 50.

312
00:33:38,300 --> 00:33:42,600
By your eyes, I'd say you were kind.
So much for eyes.

313
00:33:42,700 --> 00:33:47,100
How old are you?
You brought it up. I'm curious.

314
00:33:47,300 --> 00:33:52,200
- Not that you're ugly.
- I can take the compliment.

315
00:33:52,400 --> 00:33:57,000
But my knees start knocking when
you turn on the charm full blast.

316
00:33:57,200 --> 00:34:00,800
What's with the dark?

317
00:34:03,200 --> 00:34:05,400
Dawn patrol.

318
00:34:05,600 --> 00:34:09,400
My son had
a full-blown attack.

319
00:34:09,500 --> 00:34:14,900
And for extra fun
they gave us the wrong antibiotics.

320
00:34:15,100 --> 00:34:17,900
No!

321
00:34:18,100 --> 00:34:22,200
It's bacon for the dog.

322
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:28,300
Last week I was playing the piano
for him. And he likes it.

323
00:34:28,400 --> 00:34:34,900
So I decide
I'm going to make a little joke.

324
00:34:43,800 --> 00:34:48,100
It's a beautiful day for our walk.

325
00:35:00,100 --> 00:35:03,700
Look at that dog.

326
00:35:03,900 --> 00:35:08,900
I've got to give you
something real good.

327
00:35:09,400 --> 00:35:13,200
I'm going to show it to you.

328
00:35:14,400 --> 00:35:17,400
Don't be like me.

329
00:35:17,500 --> 00:35:23,300
Stay as you are. You're perfect.
I'll get you something to eat.

330
00:35:25,400 --> 00:35:28,500
I'd like to be treated like that.

331
00:35:29,900 --> 00:35:34,200
Let's go home and do some writing.

332
00:35:35,500 --> 00:35:40,200
''He had made the girl happy.
And what a girl.''

333
00:35:40,600 --> 00:35:44,100
''You've saved my life, she said.''

334
00:35:45,600 --> 00:35:49,100
''You'd better make it up to me.''

335
00:35:51,900 --> 00:35:57,900
Done!
Yes, I hate the doggie.

336
00:35:59,100 --> 00:36:02,400
62 books. Done.

337
00:36:03,100 --> 00:36:08,600
- We have to cut back all expenses.
- He has no medical insurance?

338
00:36:08,800 --> 00:36:13,800
These are the food receipts,
the household expenses.

339
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:17,800
- Here's one for the dog again.
- I got it.

340
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:21,000
And all the laundry.

341
00:36:23,200 --> 00:36:30,000
Boy, look at that.
He likes it at Chez Melvin.

342
00:36:31,400 --> 00:36:35,900
What are you coming over here for?
I can't cook with a dog near me.

343
00:36:36,100 --> 00:36:42,500
Just sit. We don't want any company.
I'll read you Emerson.

344
00:36:54,100 --> 00:37:00,000
- How's Verdell doing?
- He's a pain in the ass.

345
00:37:03,800 --> 00:37:10,400
Simon's home. Can you keep the dog
until he's had a chance to adjust?

346
00:37:10,600 --> 00:37:15,200
It's been weeks and weeks.
A few more won't matter.

347
00:37:15,400 --> 00:37:20,900
He wants him back right away.
He'll be by tomorrow.

348
00:37:22,700 --> 00:37:26,500
Okay.

349
00:37:32,000 --> 00:37:35,300
Hungry? Be right with you.

350
00:38:38,800 --> 00:38:40,700
Mr. Udall.

351
00:38:46,200 --> 00:38:50,600
Some face they left hanging on you.
You look like ...

352
00:38:50,800 --> 00:38:54,600
Could you take it ...

353
00:38:55,500 --> 00:38:58,800
... just a little easy, Mr. Udall?

354
00:39:02,000 --> 00:39:04,000
Thank you.

355
00:39:06,700 --> 00:39:09,100
Verdell.

356
00:39:10,500 --> 00:39:14,700
Come here, my beautiful boy.
Come here.

357
00:39:14,900 --> 00:39:18,300
Let's go home and get well.

358
00:39:19,400 --> 00:39:24,400
I can't blame him for being weird.
Look at yourself in the mirror.

359
00:39:28,900 --> 00:39:31,100
Thank you.

360
00:39:34,300 --> 00:39:37,300
Come on, sweetheart.

361
00:39:37,500 --> 00:39:40,800
Verdell, come here.

362
00:39:43,000 --> 00:39:46,000
I know what you want.

363
00:39:49,600 --> 00:39:52,200
Where's my boy?

364
00:39:57,600 --> 00:40:01,400
No, don't force him.

365
00:40:33,100 --> 00:40:37,600
Over a dog!

366
00:40:38,200 --> 00:40:41,800
Over an ugly dog.

367
00:40:48,900 --> 00:40:53,700
Worst sidewalk in New York.
Look where they put it.

368
00:41:00,200 --> 00:41:05,200
- Help!
- You'll make an appointment.

369
00:41:05,300 --> 00:41:09,300
How can you diagnose someone as
an obsessive-compulsive disorder -

370
00:41:09,500 --> 00:41:12,500
- and then act like I had a choice
about barging in?

371
00:41:12,700 --> 00:41:16,100
- You must leave.
- You said you could help me.

372
00:41:16,300 --> 00:41:21,700
- What was that? A tease?
- If you take responsibility ...

373
00:41:21,900 --> 00:41:25,900
- You changed the room around.
- Two years ago.

374
00:41:26,100 --> 00:41:30,100
I also grew a beard, but you're
not interested in changes in me.

375
00:41:30,300 --> 00:41:34,200
I don't have a mountain of time.
I have to get to my restaurant.

376
00:41:34,400 --> 00:41:38,700
Do you know how hard it was for me
to come here?

377
00:41:40,100 --> 00:41:42,500
No, we're not doing this now.

378
00:41:42,700 --> 00:41:47,800
I changed just one pattern,
as you always said I should.

379
00:41:48,000 --> 00:41:50,400
No. Nope.

380
00:41:59,600 --> 00:42:04,400
What if this is
as good as it gets?

381
00:42:16,200 --> 00:42:19,400
What the heck are those for?

382
00:42:21,300 --> 00:42:24,500
No, no, no. Get Carol.

383
00:42:24,600 --> 00:42:30,500
I'm filling in. She might be getting
a job closer to home.

384
00:42:32,800 --> 00:42:37,100
- Why plastic?
- What are you trying to do to me?

385
00:42:37,300 --> 00:42:41,400
- What do you mean?
- Look, elephant girl.

386
00:42:41,600 --> 00:42:47,200
Go get Carol or something.
Just have her do my one meal here.

387
00:42:47,400 --> 00:42:50,400
I'll pay whatever you want.

388
00:42:52,800 --> 00:42:55,100
Do it!

389
00:42:57,700 --> 00:43:01,200
Bryan. Code blue.

390
00:43:06,500 --> 00:43:10,900
Out! Just shut up and get out.

391
00:43:11,600 --> 00:43:17,800
I'll be quiet.
Just let me stay here. No problem.

392
00:43:18,000 --> 00:43:22,300
Go get Carol.

393
00:43:22,800 --> 00:43:28,000
I'm not a prick.
You are. I'm not judging.

394
00:43:28,200 --> 00:43:33,300
This day has been a disaster.

395
00:43:34,100 --> 00:43:37,900
- I'm not sure if I can handle this.
- Get out!

396
00:43:38,900 --> 00:43:45,400
Get out immediately
or there's going to be trouble.

397
00:44:00,600 --> 00:44:02,700
See you.

398
00:44:03,800 --> 00:44:06,100
It's about time.

399
00:44:08,000 --> 00:44:13,500
- Carol's last name?
- Connelly.

400
00:44:21,200 --> 00:44:25,000
- Does he visit often?
- Not really. Not any more.

401
00:45:15,500 --> 00:45:18,300
I'm hungry.

402
00:45:18,500 --> 00:45:21,800
You've ruined my whole day.
I haven't eaten.

403
00:45:21,900 --> 00:45:26,100
- What are you doing here?
- This is not a sexist thing ...

404
00:45:26,200 --> 00:45:29,600
Are you totally gone?
This is my home.

405
00:45:31,800 --> 00:45:37,400
I'm trying to keep emotion aside,
even though it's important.

406
00:45:37,600 --> 00:45:42,600
- I have strong feelings on this.
- What?

407
00:45:42,700 --> 00:45:48,700
That I wasn't there? Do you have
any control over how creepy you get?

408
00:45:54,500 --> 00:45:58,300
Yes, I do.

409
00:45:59,100 --> 00:46:04,900
And to prove it ... I have not
gotten personal, and you have.

410
00:46:05,700 --> 00:46:10,000
Why aren't you at work?
Are you sick?

411
00:46:12,100 --> 00:46:15,500
You don't look sick.

412
00:46:16,100 --> 00:46:19,800
Just tired and bitter.

413
00:46:21,800 --> 00:46:25,000
My son is sick.

414
00:46:27,500 --> 00:46:30,400
What about your mother?

415
00:46:30,900 --> 00:46:36,500
- How do you know about her?
- I hear you talking while I wait.

416
00:46:36,600 --> 00:46:40,700
- Mom, I finished my juice.
- One sec.

417
00:46:49,800 --> 00:46:52,100
How are you doing?

418
00:46:57,800 --> 00:47:00,100
You should answer me.

419
00:47:00,300 --> 00:47:05,100
Sorry, Melvin. I can't handle you
teaching my son manners.

420
00:47:08,000 --> 00:47:10,500
Back to life.

421
00:47:18,000 --> 00:47:20,800
What's wrong?

422
00:47:20,900 --> 00:47:27,200
Five one-thousand,
four one-thousand ...

423
00:47:30,000 --> 00:47:34,000
- 104.9.
- We're going on a cab ride.

424
00:47:36,100 --> 00:47:39,400
Look out, you guys!

425
00:47:40,500 --> 00:47:44,900
Look out.
We're okay. We're okay.

426
00:47:46,600 --> 00:47:49,200
Melvin! Wait!

427
00:47:50,200 --> 00:47:53,200
Melvin! Wait!

428
00:47:58,800 --> 00:48:02,100
Shut up, kids!

429
00:48:02,700 --> 00:48:05,800
Give us a lift, would you?

430
00:48:09,900 --> 00:48:13,300
Cover your mouth when you cough.

431
00:48:15,000 --> 00:48:20,600
- Brooklyn Presbyterian Hospital.
- Hospital?

432
00:48:21,100 --> 00:48:26,400
- Any chance you'll be back today?
- No! Stay away from me.

433
00:48:30,900 --> 00:48:36,700
We can't put this off any longer.
I feel terrible that I have to ...

434
00:48:37,100 --> 00:48:41,500
Could you just leave the dog
for a second?

435
00:48:43,300 --> 00:48:46,100
Sorry.

436
00:48:48,900 --> 00:48:54,000
- What are those cards?
- Frank thought I should have notes.

437
00:48:55,000 --> 00:49:00,000
So I would maintain focus
and not terrify you.

438
00:49:00,200 --> 00:49:05,500
See? He's right.
I need the cards.

439
00:49:05,700 --> 00:49:07,400
SlMON, YOU'RE BROKE

440
00:49:14,200 --> 00:49:19,100
The medical bills are 61,000 now.
And the show didn't go well.

441
00:49:19,200 --> 00:49:24,200
I spoke to your parents.
They didn't hang up or anything.

442
00:49:24,400 --> 00:49:28,300
But they'd feel strange calling you.

443
00:49:28,500 --> 00:49:33,100
I can't call them. Come here, baby.

444
00:49:34,300 --> 00:49:36,300
Come here.

445
00:49:36,500 --> 00:49:40,400
Verdell? What's wrong?

446
00:49:40,600 --> 00:49:45,100
You miss the tough guy?
Well, here I am.

447
00:49:45,300 --> 00:49:50,300
Happy to see me, you little mop?
How about a ride down the chute?

448
00:49:50,400 --> 00:49:53,200
I'm sorry. I didn't mean that.

449
00:49:53,300 --> 00:49:56,100
I didn't mean that, sweetheart.

450
00:49:56,200 --> 00:49:57,900
Sorry ...

451
00:49:59,400 --> 00:50:04,800
I'll be able to keep my apartment
and the studio, won't I?

452
00:50:07,400 --> 00:50:11,400
Oh, my God!

453
00:50:41,300 --> 00:50:45,700
Yes, you make us a lot of money.
But it's more appropriate ...

454
00:50:45,800 --> 00:50:52,700
I need this.
Just say, ''Melvin, I'll try.''

455
00:50:55,500 --> 00:50:59,400
- Melvin, I'll try.
- Thank you.

456
00:50:59,600 --> 00:51:06,000
My son just got accepted to Brown.
My husband was dying.

457
00:51:06,100 --> 00:51:12,000
Good, nice, thrilled, exciting.
You don't have to wait with me.

458
00:51:19,800 --> 00:51:27,300
I can't resist. I just have
so many questions I want to ask you.

459
00:51:27,500 --> 00:51:31,700
You have no idea
what your work means to me.

460
00:51:31,900 --> 00:51:34,500
What does it mean to you?

461
00:51:34,800 --> 00:51:39,400
That somebody out there knows
what it's like to be in here.

462
00:51:40,600 --> 00:51:43,100
God, this is like a nightmare.

463
00:51:43,800 --> 00:51:47,900
Come on.
Just a couple of questions.

464
00:51:51,200 --> 00:51:55,500
- How do you write women so well?
- I think of a man.

465
00:51:55,700 --> 00:52:00,300
And I take away reason
and accountability.

466
00:52:31,700 --> 00:52:34,100
- Mom!
- ln here, Mrs. Connelly.

467
00:52:34,300 --> 00:52:37,500
- Please, what?
- I'm ...

468
00:52:37,700 --> 00:52:40,300
- Tell me!
- Dr. Bettes.

469
00:52:40,500 --> 00:52:45,400
- Not your name. Where is he?
- He's in the bathroom.

470
00:52:46,000 --> 00:52:50,500
What's wrong? You know there are
doctors that come to your house?

471
00:52:50,600 --> 00:52:53,400
I'm home.

472
00:52:53,600 --> 00:52:57,900
I didn't know you had an admirer.
Oh, you met the gift.

473
00:52:59,100 --> 00:53:02,300
He's good. I'm an expert on doctors.

474
00:53:02,500 --> 00:53:05,500
Okay, doctor?

475
00:53:05,700 --> 00:53:09,400
My wife is
Melvin Udall's publisher.

476
00:53:09,600 --> 00:53:14,900
I'm to take care of this little guy
because you are needed at work.

477
00:53:15,100 --> 00:53:19,400
- What kind of work do you do?
- I'm a waitress.

478
00:53:19,700 --> 00:53:23,600
- ln Manhattan.
- Dr. Bettes?

479
00:53:23,800 --> 00:53:26,300
Excuse me.

480
00:53:27,800 --> 00:53:32,100
- I'm sorry it took so long.
- I couldn't find it, either.

481
00:53:32,300 --> 00:53:38,700
Could you get this to the lab?
I want it back today.

482
00:53:38,900 --> 00:53:45,100
- Did you say ''today''?
- Yes. Let's sit down.

483
00:53:46,000 --> 00:53:51,500
These are the receipts from
all the prescriptions for the year.

484
00:53:51,700 --> 00:53:57,400
- The calendar.
- This is a calendar of days.

485
00:53:57,500 --> 00:54:00,700
- And how he felt.
- Good.

486
00:54:00,900 --> 00:54:05,500
- How long has he had the problem?
- Since forever. Six months old.

487
00:54:05,700 --> 00:54:08,400
Have they done blood tests?

488
00:54:08,600 --> 00:54:12,400
- When he was well?
- No.

489
00:54:12,500 --> 00:54:15,800
- And how about skin testing?
- No.

490
00:54:16,000 --> 00:54:19,000
- No standard scratch test?
- No.

491
00:54:19,200 --> 00:54:24,800
They said my plan didn't cover it.
Why? Should they have?

492
00:54:26,200 --> 00:54:29,300
