01:52:08,100 --> 01:52:13,000
We'll probably have a five-hour
drive. It'll give us a chance to ...

976
01:52:14,700 --> 01:52:18,100
- I'm coming.
- What about your parents?

977
01:52:18,300 --> 01:52:22,100
- No. I'll take care of myself.
- What are you talking about?

978
01:52:22,200 --> 01:52:27,500
- You've got real problems.
- I know. I'm a little bit nervous.

979
01:52:27,600 --> 01:52:31,300
Suddenly everything seems so easy.

980
01:52:31,700 --> 01:52:35,300
Carol, a load has been lifted.

981
01:52:37,700 --> 01:52:41,000
- One night wih me.
- You think you're kidding.

982
01:52:45,100 --> 01:52:50,400
- No choice.
- I've got a gift for you.

983
01:52:50,600 --> 01:52:54,400
Let me see ... Gorgeous.

984
01:52:55,300 --> 01:53:00,000
Do it. And get the dog picked up. I
can't believe he let it stay there.

985
01:53:00,200 --> 01:53:03,000
Goodbye.

986
01:53:03,200 --> 01:53:05,400
Your luck's running.

987
01:53:05,500 --> 01:53:10,700
They sub-let your place.
You're homeless.

988
01:53:10,800 --> 01:53:16,500
- Frank's got a line on a new place.
- Where?

989
01:53:17,200 --> 01:53:20,700
Does it matter?

990
01:53:21,800 --> 01:53:24,800
No, it doesn't.

991
01:53:25,700 --> 01:53:28,800
I'm fine. Like the hat?

992
01:53:29,900 --> 01:53:31,700
I'm sorry.

993
01:53:46,800 --> 01:53:49,200
FOR EMERGENCY USE ONLY

994
01:54:04,400 --> 01:54:09,700
- I don't want to hear that music.
- You said you liked it.

995
01:54:12,100 --> 01:54:18,500
- This one has a meaning.
- I don't want to hear it.

996
01:54:40,800 --> 01:54:45,000
Here's the keys to my apartment.

997
01:54:45,100 --> 01:54:49,400
Go up there and wait
and I'll take Carol home.

998
01:54:49,600 --> 01:54:54,100
- I'll take a bus.
- No, I'll take you.

999
01:54:59,500 --> 01:55:02,400
Can you come here?

1000
01:55:02,600 --> 01:55:06,400
- I don't care what you did for me.
- What's wrong?

1001
01:55:06,600 --> 01:55:12,000
I don't want to know you any more.
All you do is make me feel bad.

1002
01:55:15,300 --> 01:55:18,300
You have my number.

1003
01:55:19,700 --> 01:55:23,800
- Let him take you home.
- Don't want to.

1004
01:55:24,900 --> 01:55:28,100
- I love you.
- I love you too.

1005
01:55:36,600 --> 01:55:39,300
Don't say anything.

1006
01:55:42,900 --> 01:55:48,300
I've got to get a hold of Frank
and see where I'm hanging my hat.

1007
01:55:49,300 --> 01:55:53,000
I think you're going to
have to camp it here.

1008
01:55:53,200 --> 01:55:56,500
There's Verdell!

1009
01:56:04,700 --> 01:56:08,300
Mommy and Daddy are home.

1010
01:56:09,800 --> 01:56:14,100
Sorry. You're fun to mess with.

1011
01:56:15,200 --> 01:56:20,600
They rented your place furnished.
Jackie said she'd bring your things.

1012
01:56:20,700 --> 01:56:25,600
They were going to set you up
in here. It's an extra room.

1013
01:56:25,800 --> 01:56:30,800
- It's got good light.
- I'm coming.

1014
01:56:35,700 --> 01:56:39,700
It's nice. Looks good.

1015
01:56:39,900 --> 01:56:47,500
They've even got your music,
paintings, paints.

1016
01:56:47,700 --> 01:56:50,100
I have to say they did a good job.

1017
01:56:52,900 --> 01:56:59,100
It's going to be okay.
Cosy, huh?

1018
01:57:03,900 --> 01:57:08,400
Thank you, Melvin.
You overwhelm me.

1019
01:57:15,700 --> 01:57:19,500
I love you.

1020
01:57:23,600 --> 01:57:30,300
I'd be the luckiest guy alive
if that did it for me.

1021
01:57:42,400 --> 01:57:46,100
Make yourself at home.

1022
01:57:47,400 --> 01:57:50,000
Anything else in the bag?

1023
01:57:50,200 --> 01:57:54,000
But I was playing soccer
while you were away.

1024
01:57:54,100 --> 01:57:57,600
I love my cookbook.

1025
01:57:57,800 --> 01:58:02,800
It's got wonderful recipes.
It says something with a shark.

1026
01:58:03,000 --> 01:58:08,200
Shark with a bite.
Would you like that, Spencer?

1027
01:58:08,400 --> 01:58:11,100
And some cookies here
called Wasps' Nests.

1028
01:58:14,500 --> 01:58:18,000
Where is my big hairy boy?

1029
01:58:18,200 --> 01:58:23,000
Where is he?
Where is my beautiful boy?

1030
01:58:23,100 --> 01:58:25,300
Sweetheart!

1031
01:58:25,500 --> 01:58:28,900
- Oh, you're in bed.
- No, no.

1032
01:58:32,300 --> 01:58:39,500
I just didn't think Verdell should
get too comfortable sleeping here.

1033
01:58:39,700 --> 01:58:43,400
The dog's already comfortable.

1034
01:58:47,400 --> 01:58:49,300
ls this okay?

1035
01:58:51,300 --> 01:58:54,800
Hello ... Hi, it's me.

1036
01:58:55,300 --> 01:59:00,600
He took me in.
It's Carol for you.

1037
01:59:00,700 --> 01:59:05,600
- Jackie brought it all over ...
- Just take the dog.

1038
01:59:06,600 --> 01:59:08,500
Take the dog.

1039
01:59:11,900 --> 01:59:17,400
- Come on. Move fast. Don't limp.
- Good luck.

1040
01:59:33,800 --> 01:59:36,900
- Howare you doing?
- Not so hot.

1041
01:59:37,100 --> 01:59:42,800
- Why? What's wrong?
- Was I sensible or hard on you?

1042
01:59:43,100 --> 01:59:49,400
- Maybe both.
- Are you being cute or crazy now?

1043
01:59:49,600 --> 01:59:54,200
- Cute.
- You don't have to answer.

1044
01:59:54,400 --> 01:59:56,900
Just listen to me.

1045
01:59:57,600 --> 02:00:01,900
It's really something
that you're looking after Simon.

1046
02:00:02,100 --> 02:00:07,800
And what I said on the street ...
That was a bad thing to say.

1047
02:00:08,000 --> 02:00:14,100
It made me sick to my stomach.
It was a bad thing to say.

1048
02:00:14,500 --> 02:00:19,200
And I'd be lying if I didn't say
I enjoy your company.

1049
02:00:20,800 --> 02:00:26,900
But you do bother me.
And I know it's better for me ...

1050
02:00:27,100 --> 02:00:31,700
... to not have contact with you
because you're not ready.

1051
02:00:31,900 --> 02:00:36,400
You're an old guy to not be ready.
And I'm too old to ignore that.

1052
02:00:36,600 --> 02:00:42,300
But there were extraordinary
kindnesses that did take place.

1053
02:00:49,000 --> 02:00:51,900
Anyway. Thanks for the trip.

1054
02:00:53,700 --> 02:00:56,000
Goodnight.

1055
02:00:56,200 --> 02:00:59,300
Okay if I say something now?

1056
02:01:03,300 --> 02:01:05,900
Go ahead.

1057
02:01:06,900 --> 02:01:11,100
I should have danced with you.

1058
02:01:14,200 --> 02:01:17,700
Goodnight.

1059
02:01:37,200 --> 02:01:41,800
- Are you going to talk to me?
- I'm coming.

1060
02:01:52,200 --> 02:01:57,300
- What did she say?
- That I'm a great guy.

1061
02:01:57,400 --> 02:02:01,700
And she doesn't want
contact with me.

1062
02:02:02,800 --> 02:02:05,700
I'm dying here.

1063
02:02:07,000 --> 02:02:12,900
- Because ... you love her.
- No.

1064
02:02:13,100 --> 02:02:16,300
And you people
are supposed to be sensitive?

1065
02:02:16,500 --> 02:02:20,900
Then you tell me why.
You're the one who's ''dying here''.

1066
02:02:21,100 --> 02:02:24,800
- Let me sleep on it.
- Oh, come on.

1067
02:02:24,900 --> 02:02:28,700
- I'll figure it out.
- Please ...

1068
02:02:30,100 --> 02:02:36,500
I'm stuck.
I can't get back to my old life.

1069
02:02:38,700 --> 02:02:43,600
- She's evicted me from my life.
- Did you really like it that much?

1070
02:02:43,700 --> 02:02:47,000
It's better than this.

1071
02:02:47,100 --> 02:02:51,600
If you're going to give me hope,
you've got to do better.

1072
02:02:51,700 --> 02:02:55,600
If you can't be mildly interesting,
then shut up.

1073
02:02:55,800 --> 02:02:59,800
I'm drowning here!
And you're describing the water.

1074
02:03:00,000 --> 02:03:03,100
Picking on me won't help.

1075
02:03:04,200 --> 02:03:08,100
If that's true,
I'm really in trouble.

1076
02:03:08,200 --> 02:03:12,300
Do you know where you're lucky?

1077
02:03:17,000 --> 02:03:20,700
You know who you want.

1078
02:03:20,900 --> 02:03:26,900
I would take your seat any day.
Do something. Go over there.

1079
02:03:27,100 --> 02:03:32,400
Tonight. It's not always good
to let things calm down.

1080
02:03:32,600 --> 02:03:36,600
You can do this, Melvin.

1081
02:03:36,800 --> 02:03:40,000
Tell her how you feel.

1082
02:03:40,200 --> 02:03:44,400
- I'm charged.
- Yes, you are.

1083
02:03:44,600 --> 02:03:49,200
- She might kill me if I go there.
- Then stay. I'll read you a story.

1084
02:03:49,300 --> 02:03:55,100
The best thing going for you is your
willingness to humiliate yourself.

1085
02:03:55,300 --> 02:03:59,100
Go over there.
Do this. Catch her off guard.

1086
02:04:08,900 --> 02:04:11,500
Thanks a lot.

1087
02:04:13,200 --> 02:04:16,000
Here I go.

1088
02:04:25,000 --> 02:04:27,800
What's wrong?

1089
02:04:29,400 --> 02:04:32,600
I forgot to lock the door.

1090
02:05:50,800 --> 02:05:54,500
- What do you want?
- I'm sorry I woke you up.

1091
02:05:54,600 --> 02:05:57,900
I wasn't asleep.

1092
02:06:01,300 --> 02:06:04,300
What a break.

1093
02:06:05,200 --> 02:06:08,900
ls it a secret
what you're doing here?

1094
02:06:11,200 --> 02:06:14,100
I had to see you.

1095
02:06:17,300 --> 02:06:19,600
Because?

1096
02:06:22,000 --> 02:06:26,000
It relaxes me.

1097
02:06:26,500 --> 02:06:30,600
I'd feel better sitting outside
your apartment on the curb -

1098
02:06:30,800 --> 02:06:35,200
- than any other place
I can think of or imagine.

1099
02:06:35,400 --> 02:06:38,000
That's overstating.

1100
02:06:38,200 --> 02:06:44,100
I'd rather be sitting inside so I
don't get my feet in the gutter.

1101
02:06:44,200 --> 02:06:49,800
Stop. Why can't I just have
a normal boyfriend? Why?

1102
02:06:49,900 --> 02:06:53,700
A regular boyfriend
who doesn't go nuts on me.

1103
02:06:53,900 --> 02:06:57,200
Everybody wants that.
It doesn't exist.

1104
02:07:00,900 --> 02:07:06,000
I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to interrupt.

1105
02:07:12,100 --> 02:07:15,300
Boyfriend ...

1106
02:07:18,200 --> 02:07:23,500
Come on in and try
not to ruin everything by being you.

1107
02:07:23,700 --> 02:07:27,900
Maybe we could live
without the wisecracks?

1108
02:07:31,200 --> 02:07:35,000
Maybe we could.

1109
02:07:59,900 --> 02:08:04,900
It feels a little confined here.
Let's take a walk.

1110
02:08:07,800 --> 02:08:13,400
It's four in the morning.
A walk sounds a little screwy to me.

1111
02:08:14,200 --> 02:08:19,400
- If you don't mind.
- Well, if you need an excuse ...

1112
02:08:20,200 --> 02:08:24,400
There's a bakery on the corner
that'll be open soon.

1113
02:08:24,600 --> 02:08:30,400
That way we're not screwy,
but two people that like warm rolls.

1114
02:08:54,700 --> 02:09:01,100
- What are you doing?
- I want you to hear that song.

1115
02:09:08,500 --> 02:09:13,300
And darling
I'm neverlonely

1116
02:09:13,500 --> 02:09:17,000
wheneveryou're in sight...

1117
02:09:17,800 --> 02:09:19,800
Thank you.

1118
02:09:21,300 --> 02:09:24,600
I was ...

1119
02:09:38,500 --> 02:09:43,800
I'm sorry.
Whatever this is won't work.

1120
02:09:52,200 --> 02:09:54,600
- I'm ...
- What?

1121
02:09:56,800 --> 02:09:59,600
I'm feeling better.

1122
02:09:59,800 --> 02:10:06,600
It may seem that way now,
but you don't know me all that well.

1123
02:10:07,500 --> 02:10:10,600
I'm not the answer for you.

1124
02:10:10,700 --> 02:10:14,800
- I've got a compliment for you.
- You know what?

1125
02:10:15,000 --> 02:10:18,900
Let me talk.

1126
02:10:25,500 --> 02:10:29,200
I might be the only person
on the earth -

1127
02:10:29,400 --> 02:10:32,400
- that knows
you're the greatest woman on earth.

1128
02:10:32,600 --> 02:10:40,200
I might be the only one who knows
how amazing you are.

1129
02:10:40,500 --> 02:10:44,700
And how you are with Spencer.
Spence.

1130
02:10:45,900 --> 02:10:50,100
And in every single thought
you have.

1131
02:10:50,300 --> 02:10:57,000
How you almost always mean something
that's about being straight or good.

1132
02:10:58,300 --> 02:11:02,100
Most people miss that about you.

1133
02:11:02,400 --> 02:11:07,600
I wonder how they can watch you
bring their food and clear tables -

1134
02:11:07,800 --> 02:11:12,100
- and never get that they just met
the greatest woman alive.

1135
02:11:12,300 --> 02:11:17,400
And the fact that I get it
makes me feel good ...

1136
02:11:18,300 --> 02:11:22,600
... about me.

1137
02:11:29,000 --> 02:11:35,400
ls that something
that it's bad for you to be around?

1138
02:11:44,600 --> 02:11:47,000
No.

1139
02:11:49,800 --> 02:11:53,000
I'm going to grab you?

1140
02:11:53,200 --> 02:11:57,900
I didn't mean for that to be
a question. I'm going to grab you.

1141
02:12:21,400 --> 02:12:24,200
I know I can do better than that.

1142
02:12:47,700 --> 02:12:51,600
Better. Definitely better.

1143
02:12:55,600 --> 02:12:58,600
See?

1144
02:13:12,600 --> 02:13:17,300
- Want something?
- Warm rolls.

1145
02:13:25,800 --> 02:13:28,100
Excuse us.